website_content.content:
The claim: Joe Biden uses actor Arthur Roberts as a body double
---------------------------------------------------------------
An Oct. 17 Instagram post (, ) claims veteran actor Arthur Roberts has secretly been Joe Biden‚Äôs body double.
‚ÄúThe title of the video in Arthur‚Äôs acting credit is ‚ÄòJoe Biden Sworn in as U.S. President on Inauguration Day 2021,‚Äô‚Äù a man says in an embedded video, as an image of a screenshot from IMDB.com appears. ‚ÄúNow when you go to this page, it‚Äôs not there no more. It‚Äôs been erased. But we got screenshots.‚Äù
The post was liked more than 300 times in a day.
**Follow us on Facebook!**
Our rating: False
-----------------
There is no evidence that President Joe Biden has a body double. Roberts has no association with Biden and has never appeared as him, according to the actor‚Äôs representative.
Body double claim is baseless
-----------------------------
Roberts, an 85-year-old actor, has numerous stage, screen and film credits, according to his  and . None of those roles involved playing Biden, and he has no connection to the president.
‚ÄúIt is not true,‚Äù said , a manager with Studio Talent Group, which represents Roberts. ‚ÄúArthur is an actor. He is in his 80s, but he does auditions all the time and he gets roles and he works in the film and TV industry. And he would never even have time...[Content truncated]

Now: Do you know where Kate Middleton is?
Molly Roberts writes that the conspiracy theorizing over the ‚Äúdisappearance‚Äù of the Princess of Wales reached fever pitch this week when Kensington Palace put out a photo of Kate and her kids in honor of British Mother‚Äôs Day and British Princess Is Still Alive Day.
One need not have had one‚Äôs monocle on to see how obviously the photo was manipulated ‚Äî bent lines, blurred borders, fuzzy textures, inconsistent depth of field. My favorite tweeted piece of proof:
not to be too conspiratorial, but one very odd detail I noticed on close inspection: that all these people appear to happy and having a good time, despite being obviously British pic.twitter.com/rj0m1X8BAw
Kate (or someone tweeting as Kate) eventually claimed credit for editing the image, most likely, Molly writes, using photo software‚Äôs new AI tools.
Molly buys the explanation but writes that it has problems of its own: The more we incorporate these little manipulations into our lives, the more we need to question everything we see online. And then that questioning can be taken to excess, too, to convince people that nothing can be trusted.
As Molly writes, ‚ÄúCatherine edited a photo, maybe a little, maybe a lot, and apparently, this is evidence that, next time we see her, we‚Äôll be seeing a body double instead.‚Äù

Trinitarios Gang Member Charged in Connection With Two Shootings in Queens and Brooklyn on the Same Day
Abel Mora, a member of the Trinitarios‚Äîa violent street gang‚Äîwas charge with being a convicted felon in possession of ammunition related to two separate shootings Mora allegedly committed in Queens and Brooklyn on August 13, 2023.¬†¬†
If convicted, Mora faces up to 15 years in prison on each of the two counts.
"Gang members like Mora continue to plague our city with his blatant disregard for the safety of our community and his reckless indifference to human life. It is only through our local and federal partnerships that we are able to put a stop to these violent repeat offenders," stated FBI New York Assistant Director-in-Charge Smith. "This case is another example of how the FBI and our law enforcement partners are dedicated to keeping the streets of New York City safe for everyone in our community."
Full press release
Twelve Charged in Connection with Violent Motorcycle Gang Assault
A dozen members of the Homietos Outlaw Motorcycle Gang are now in custody on racketeering and firearms charges related to a violent assault of another motorcycle club in Houston.
All 12 are charged with assault with a dangerous weapon in aid of racketeering and conspiracy to do so and discharging a firearm during a crime of violence.
"The arrests of 12 alleged Homieto outlaw motorcycle gang members are the result of a multi-year FBI Houston-led interagency investigation and are the first significant indictments against these types of criminal groups in the Houston area," said FBI Houston Acting Special Agent in Charge David Martinez. "This criminal organization is accused of crimes that keep victims, community members and rivals in a perpetual state of fear through intimidation and violence. Law enforcement and the public have had enough of the violence, ruthlessness and disregard for law and order that this gang is alleged to have perpetrated."
